# Floor Plan Tool — Android App Conversion

## Phase 1: Project Scaffold
- [ ] Create Android project with Gradle (Kotlin + Compose + Material 3)
- [ ] Set up project structure: packages for model, viewmodel, ui, renderer, util
- [ ] Configure dependencies (Compose, Serialization, PDF, testing)

## Phase 2: Data Model & Core Logic
- [ ] Define data classes: `PlanDocument`, `Annotation`, `RefAnchors`, `PointD`, `OffsetD`, `AnnoType`
- [ ] Implement camera transforms: `screenToPlan`, `planToScreen`, `fitToScreen`, `zoomAt`
- [ ] Implement re-register transform math
- [ ] Implement clustering logic
- [ ] Implement JSON serialization/deserialization

## Phase 3: Renderer
- [ ] Create `FloorPlanRenderer` class (draws to any Canvas)
- [ ] Draw base plan bitmap
- [ ] Draw grid overlay (calibrated, with thresholds)
- [ ] Draw crosshairs with rings + cluster counts
- [ ] Draw label boxes + leader lines (RED)
- [ ] Draw A4 overlay
- [ ] Draw mode-specific helpers (rubber bands, distance tags)
- [ ] Draw reference anchors

## Phase 4: UI & Interactions
- [ ] Main screen layout: TopBar + Canvas + BottomSheet
- [ ] Mode selection UI
- [ ] Annotation inputs (name, details, type, crosshair size)
- [ ] Gesture handling: pinch zoom, pan, tap, long-press
- [ ] Mode-dependent tap handling (calibration, annotation, place1/2, reregister)
- [ ] Label hit-testing, selection, dragging
- [ ] Edit dialog (long-press or edit button)
- [ ] Quick actions: Fit, Zoom In/Out, Grid toggle, A4 toggle
- [ ] Delete selected annotation

## Phase 5: Import/Export
- [ ] Image import via SAF
- [ ] PDF import via PdfRenderer (page 1, quality setting)
- [ ] JSON export via SAF
- [ ] JSON import via SAF
- [ ] PNG export (offscreen render + optional details block)
- [ ] PDF export via PdfDocument

